AE=0 traps met (all four game gates byte-identical to the clean-51e4396
baselines, no re-baselining, no new patch tools):
 - Push budget vs exact vertex math: Vulkan keeps ONE premultiplied mvp
   (two mat4s would blow the 128-byte push range); the GL flavor keeps
   view_proj and model SEPARATE because the composed GL leg multiplied on
   the GPU — CPU-premultiplying moves clip coords by ULPs and every
   interpolated sample with them.
 - Associativity: GLSL `u_view_proj * u_model * vec4` is LEFT-associative
   (mat×mat first, then mat×vec). Port as
   `mul(mul(view_proj, model), v)`, not `mul(view_proj, mul(model, v))`.
 - The cubic-solver fusion patch is NOT needed here: glyph coverage is
   quadratic-only (solveMonotonicCubicRoot is dead in this family), and
   the game body's transcendental soup (sin/pow/normalize) fused
   identically under Mesa. gl_o0 IS used, like every stage-B family.
 - Records stride is a compile-time 23 in the family source;
   gl_material.zig comptime-asserts it against
   snail.render.records.BYTES_PER_INSTANCE.

